        <paragraph>
          <num>•</num>
          <content>
            <p>Policy support costs including compliance and enforcement </p>
          </content>
        </paragraph>
      </level>
      <level>
        <content>
          <p>Given the combination of household and non-household options underpinning Option 3M, we estimate it can achieve an increase in the municipal recycling rate of 8.9 percentage points (i.e., the total rate of 51.2% by 2035). </p>
        </content>
      </level>
      <level>
        <content>
          <p>For Option 3M, the carbon savings are estimated to be £9,165m (i.e., 32.3Mt CO2e) over the appraisal period.  </p>
        </content>
      </level>
      <level>
        <content>
          <p>Option 3M has the same policy support costs as Option 1M and 2M. They are estimated at £78m over the appraisal period. </p>
