      <level>
        <content>
          <p>Whilst this is not the main sensitivity analysis, we have modelled the effects of using higher carbon equivalent factors for methane on the municipal sector GHG savings. This difference is due to the different warming potentials of methane at different temperatures (i.e., AR 4 and AR 5 without/with feedback); and only affects our calculations on non-traded emissions in our impact assessment.</p>
        </content>
      </level>
      <level>
        <content>
          <p>Our central calculations are based on AR4, based on guidance from BEIS (former departmental name), but it is very likely that this guidance will be updated to require to use one of the AR5 values.</p>
        </content>
